EP  - 319
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/04/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(87)90087-3
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387887900873
AB  - The focus of this study of disease control is on the following two questions: (1) What level of disease treatment represents an economically sound target? (2) What combination of preventive and curative measures is most cost efficient in reaching and maintaining that target? A theoretical model is developed and applied to control of schistosomiasis in the People's Republic of China. The optimal strategy is found to in some cases involve delayed use of the preventive measure, allowing treatment programs time to make initial headway.
